We fix pairs 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen a,b\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 and 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen a',b'\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 in \mathchoice {\textstyle \sum _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \sum _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \sum _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \sum _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{Bx}. By  via , it suffices to exhibit identifications p\colon  a = a' and q\colon  p_* b = b'. These are given respectively by our assumptions that A and Ba' are propositions.

